Abstract
This project presents an AI-driven financial advisor that generates personalized investment portfolios based on user-defined financial goals and risk preferences. The system is built using a full-stack architecture integrating FastAPI, a web-based frontend, and an intelligent investment engine combining Constraint Satisfaction Problem (CSP), Modern Portfolio Theory (MPT), and covariance-based risk analysis.
Real-time market data is incorporated using the yfinance API, ensuring up-to-date financial decision-making. In addition, a Large Language Model (OpenAI) is used to provide clear, human-readable explanations of portfolio recommendations, improving transparency and user understanding.
The system efficiently generates constraint-compliant and risk-optimized portfolios by first filtering valid allocations using CSP and then optimizing them using MPT based on expected return, volatility, and Sharpe Ratio.
The system demonstrates improved portfolio efficiency and interpretability compared to traditional rule-based investment methods.
3. Introduction
3.1 Background of Investment Decision-Making
Investment decision-making involves allocating financial resources across assets such as stocks, bonds, and ETFs to achieve financial goals while balancing risk and return. With increasing market volatility and complexity, traditional manual approaches often become inefficient, especially for novice investors who struggle to analyze large-scale financial data.
3.2 Problem Statement
Traditional investment planning is often time-consuming, biased, and limited in its ability to process dynamic financial data. Investors face challenges in accurately evaluating risk-return trade-offs, leading to suboptimal portfolio allocation and missed financial opportunities.
3.3 Need for AI in Investment Planning
Artificial Intelligence enables data-driven and automated financial decision-making by analyzing large volumes of market data efficiently. AI-based systems reduce human bias, improve prediction accuracy, and provide personalized investment strategies tailored to individual user profiles.

3.4 Objective of the System
The objective of this system is to develop an intelligent investment advisor that generates optimized portfolios based on user constraints and financial goals. The system focuses on constraint validation, portfolio optimization, real-time market integration, and explainable AI-driven insights to support better financial decision-making.
3.5 Key Contributions of the System
Hybrid AI investment engine combining CSP + MPT + LLM
Real-time portfolio optimization using live market data
Covariance-based risk modeling for accurate diversification
Explainable AI for financial decision transparency
End-to-end full-stack implementation
4. System Overview
The system is a full-stack AI-based platform that combines constraint-based filtering with statistical optimization techniques to generate personalized investment portfolios. It consists of a frontend for user interaction, a FastAPI backend for processing, and an investment engine that applies CSP and MPT for portfolio generation and optimization. Real-time data integration and AI-based explanations enhance both accuracy and usability.
5. System Architecture
5.1 Architecture Overview
The system follows a modular architecture consisting of three primary layers: frontend, backend, and investment engine. Each layer is designed to ensure scalability, maintainability, and efficient data flow.

5.2 Architecture Explanation
The system follows a layered full-stack architecture consisting of a frontend, backend, and an AI-driven investment engine.
The frontend layer is built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript and is responsible for collecting user inputs such as financial details and displaying portfolio recommendations.
The backend layer is implemented using FastAPI, which handles API requests, processes user data, and communicates with the core investment engine.
The Investment Agent (Core Engine) is the central component of the system. It integrates multiple intelligent modules:
Constraint Satisfaction Problem (CSP): Ensures that generated portfolios satisfy user-specific constraints such as income, age, and risk tolerance.
Modern Portfolio Theory (MPT): Optimizes portfolio allocation based on expected return, volatility, and Sharpe Ratio.
Covariance Matrix Analysis: Improves risk estimation by analyzing correlations between assets.
To enhance decision-making, the system also integrates external services:
Live Market Data (yfinance): Provides real-time financial data for accurate analysis.
Large Language Model (OpenAI): Generates explanations and improves user understanding of investment recommendations.
This layered architecture ensures modularity, scalability, and efficient separation of concerns, making the system robust and extensible.
