6. Methodology
The system follows a structured pipeline combining constraint satisfaction, financial optimization, and real-time data analysis.
6.1 Constraint Satisfaction Problem (CSP)
The system first applies Constraint Satisfaction Problem (CSP) techniques to generate valid portfolio allocations based on user-defined constraints such as:
Age
Income level
Risk tolerance
Investment goals
Asset allocation limits
This ensures that all generated portfolios are realistic and aligned with user requirements.
6.2 Modern Portfolio Theory (MPT)
The valid portfolios are then optimized using Modern Portfolio Theory (MPT), which evaluates:
Expected portfolio return
Portfolio volatility (risk)
Sharpe Ratio (risk-adjusted return)
This step identifies efficient portfolios that provide the best return for a given level of risk.
6.3 Covariance Matrix
The covariance matrix is used to improve risk estimation by analyzing relationships between assets. It:
Captures correlations between asset returns
Enhances diversification analysis
Provides realistic portfolio volatility calculation
6.4 Live Market Data Integration
The system integrates real-time financial data using the yfinance API to ensure up-to-date analysis. It:
Fetches live stock prices
Retrieves historical market data
Improves accuracy of financial predictions
6.5 Large Language Model (LLM) Integration
An OpenAI-based LLM is integrated to enhance user interaction and explainability. It:
Generates human-readable investment insights
Explains portfolio recommendations
Improves user understanding of financial decisions
6.6 Optimal Portfolio Selection Using Sharpe Ratio Maximization
The final stage selects the best portfolio by maximizing the Sharpe Ratio. This ensures the chosen portfolio provides the highest return per unit of risk, leading to an optimized and efficient investment recommendation.
7. Modules Description
User Input Module:
Collects user-specific financial information such as age, income, risk tolerance, and investment objectives through the interface.
Data Processing Module:
Performs validation, cleaning, and preprocessing of user inputs to ensure consistency and accuracy before analysis.
CSP Module:
Generates feasible investment portfolios by applying constraint satisfaction rules based on user-defined financial and risk parameters.
Optimization Module (MPT):
Evaluates and ranks portfolios using Modern Portfolio Theory based on expected return, risk (volatility), and Sharpe Ratio.
Market Data Module:
Retrieves real-time and historical financial data using external APIs to support accurate portfolio evaluation.
Output Module:
Presents the final optimized portfolio along with risk metrics and AI-generated insights for better interpretability.
