13. Conclusion
The AI Investment Advisor demonstrates an effective integration of artificial intelligence and quantitative financial modeling to support intelligent investment decision-making. By combining Constraint Satisfaction Problem (CSP) for rule-based portfolio generation and Modern Portfolio Theory (MPT) with covariance-based risk analysis for optimization, the system ensures both feasibility and efficiency in portfolio construction.
The incorporation of real-time market data and Large Language Model-based explanations further enhances the system’s accuracy, transparency, and usability. Overall, the project highlights the potential of AI-driven systems in transforming traditional investment planning into a more automated, data-driven, and personalized process.
